* .NET Core Version:  .NET Core 3.0 Preview 3 3.0.100.10342 from Release branch
* Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?: No

<!-- Read https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/blob/master/Documentation/issue-guide.md -->

**Problem description:**
Unable to cast object of type ‘System.IO.MemoryStream’ to type ‘System.Drawing.Color’ in .NET Core app.

**Actual behavior:** <!-- callstack for crashes / exceptions -->
An exception pops up, and the type isn't changed successfully.
![netcoreapp](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18568603/53230246-3bb7cc80-36c1-11e9-8a28-ef97b0d6968b.png)

**Expected behavior:**
No exception and the code execute successfully.
![frameworkapp](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18568603/53230274-45d9cb00-36c1-11e9-91a2-78abd6d24107.png)

**Minimal repro:**
1.	Launch VS and create a default.NET Core app.
2.	Add the following code to Form1.cs & Form1.designer.cs, then run the app(Or you can run the attached app directly).
[NETCoreApp.zip](https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/files/2893083/NETCoreApp.zip)
[FrameworkApp.zip](https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/files/2893085/FrameworkApp.zip)
